John Alechenu, Abuja An All Progressives Congress governorship aspirant in Ondo State, Isaac Kekemeke, on Monday, promised the people of the state a better deal if given the opportunity to govern them. He made the promise during a visit to the National Secretariat of the APC, Abuja, while receiving his expression of interest and nomination forms to contest the party primary. The aspirant said his mission and vision for the state were clear. Kekemeke said, “My primary purpose of seeking the office of governor is to work with all patriots to create a prosperous and peaceful Ondo State where citizens are productively engaged to enable them live meaningful, comfortable and decent lives.” He explained that his experience as pioneer state APC chairman had equipped him with the know-how on how to manage all the tendencies within the party for optimum performance in terms of service delivery. Kekemeke further said, “It is time to fully deploy my training and acquired experience in government. To berth this new government of our dream in Ondo State, the machinery of our campaign popularly known as Lekeleke Movement is combined is committed to the practice of a new politics: the politics of ‘Ko siro, Ko sebo’ that is ‘no deceit and no rituals.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 